Comment: Congresspersons do NOT get free healthcare benefits.  
1) McCain is 80 years old and eligible for Medicare, which should cover the cost of the operation.  The same Medicare that poor folks use all the time.  Medicare Part B should cover his doctor's part of the cost;
2) If he chose to take advantage of it, McCain is eligible to purchase a Medicare supplement plan thru the Federal Employees Health Benefits (FEHB) program.  He would pay premiums for this coverage, like everyone else who buys insurance;
3) McCain is rich - he can afford to pay out of pocket for his health care - quite possibly why he 'upgraded' to have the operation at the top notch Mayo Clinic Hospital;

Uninformed rhetoric adds nothing to the discussion, nor does it offer any constructive ideas towards a solution to the healthcare/health insurance discussion, but hopefully you felt better after the rant.
